Bring a saucepan of water to a boil. Add potato and cook until tender but still firm, about 15 minutes. Drain, cool and mash. In a large bowl, combine salmon, onion, green bell pepper, potato, jalapeno, egg and ground black pepper; mix well. Shape mixture into 4 patties and coat with cracker crumbs. In a large skillet over medium heat, warm oil and cook patties until browned on each side; serve.